                    "id": "ultrafine_particle",
                    "description": "A 10 nm ultrafine particle over grassland: a small, slowly-settling particle (v_s = 7e-9 m/s) with a large Brownian diffusivity (D_diff = 5e-8 m^2/s). The high diffusivity gives a small Schmidt number Sc = 300, so the Brownian-diffusion efficiency E_B rises to ~0.046 and dominates collection (the diffusion-controlled limb of the deposition curve); the tiny Stokes number leaves E_IM and E_IN negligible. With strong collection the quasi-laminar resistance r_b drops to ~18 s/m.",
