                    "id": "coarse_particle",
                    "description": "A 10 um coarse particle over grassland: a large, fast-settling particle (v_s = 3e-3 m/s) with a small Brownian diffusivity (D_diff = 2.5e-12 m^2/s). The fast settling raises the Stokes number to St ~ 0.061, so inertial impaction E_IM (~2.4e-3) now exceeds the Brownian term E_B (~2.2e-4) — the impaction-controlled limb — while the sticking fraction R_1 falls to ~0.78 as larger Stokes numbers bring particle rebound. r_b is re-asserted at t = 1 to confirm time-invariance.",
