                {
                    "id": "impaction_and_sticking_vs_settling_velocity",
                    "description": "Inertial-impaction efficiency E_IM and sticking fraction R_1 as a function of particle settling velocity v_s, for the default grassland land-use category at u_star = 0.4 m/s. The settling velocity sets the Stokes number St = v_s*u_star/(g*A): as v_s rises, E_IM = (St/(alpha+St))^2 increases (faster particles impact more readily) while the sticking fraction R_1 = exp(-sqrt(St)) falls (faster particles rebound more). This traces the impaction-controlled limb of the Zhang et al. (2001) particle deposition curve.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
